==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insert
<hw>In*sert"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Inserted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inserting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>insertus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>inserere</ets> to insert; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in +
<ets>serere</ets> to join, connect. See <er>Series</er>.]</ety> <def>To
set within something; to put or thrust in; to introduce; to cause to
enter, or be included, or contained; <as>as, to <ex>insert</ex> a scion
in a stock; to <ex>insert</ex> a letter, word, or passage in a
composition; to <ex>insert</ex> an advertisement in a
newspaper.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These words were very weakly <qex>inserted</qex> where they will
be so liable to misconstruction.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inserted</ent>⟦br⟧
